Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
update_io_latency(25.10)                              update_io_latency(25.10)

Name
       update_io_latency  -  Provides  an  automated means of balancing IO and
       Core clock latencies after the clock network has been added to the  de-
       sign  so  that pre and post clock tree skew between the clocks is main-
       tained as closely as possible

Syntax
        update_io_latency

       [-source]

       -verbose

       Provides an automated means of balancing IO and  Core  clock  latencies
       after  the  clock  network has been added to the design so that pre and
       post clock tree skew between the clocks is  maintained  as  closely  as
       possible.  This  results  in  minimum change of inbound and outbound IO
       slacks.

       This command performs the following actions:

              * Measures and calculates ideal average latency  for  each  Core
                clock.

              * Calculates preCTS skew between IO and Core clocks.

              * Asserts  set_propagated_clock  on all clock root pins or ports
                to put clock trees in propagated mode.

              * Measures and calculates propagated mode  average  latency  for
                each Core clock.

              * Adjusts set_clock_latency on IO clocks network latency to min-
                imize pre to post CTS IO-to-Core clock skew.

       In  case  a single IO clock interacts with multiple Core clocks, the IO
       clock will be adjusted by the overall average latency of  all  the  re-
       lated Core clocks combined.

       To  be  effective,  this  command should only be used after clock trees
       have been implemented. This allows the command to see  both  the  ideal
       and propagated state of the clock trees.

       Note:  The  set_propagated_clock command should not be issued after the
       update_io_latency command.

Parameters
       -source
              Adjusts the source latency of core clock.

       -verbose
              Provides additional information to the  console  as  adjustments
              are made to each IO clock.

Related Information
              * set_propagated_clock

